This paper deals with game theory and mechanism design, which are central topics in computer science. The paper's focus on auctions and equilibria suggests that it is likely to be classified under cs.GT (Game Theory). Additionally, the paper's use of a simple game with two agents suggests that it could also be classified under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), as this subcategory often deals with multi-agent systems. The paper's focus on auctions and mechanism design also suggests that it could be classified under cs.EC (Economics and Computation). The paper's use of mathematical analysis and optimization techniques suggests that it could also be classified under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.LG (Machine Learning).
